  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Superb Service!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;ROY WARREN&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended Guy's, Gastroenterology, as an out-patient for Lactose and Lactulose Intolerance Tests, requiring a train journey of some distance from my home. The instructions and directions sent to me prior to the test were well written and accurate; the signage at the hospital clear and easily understood. 
I arrived slightly early, in need of the loo after the train journey, and the department was still closed but a very helpful member of staff, apparently unconnected with the department, arranged for me to be admitted. 
The member of staff who carried out the test was polite, friendly, with a clarity of instructions and great efficiency. 
Subsequent contact with the same department following test result problems, (that were the fault of my local hospital, NOT Guy's), brought about a very quick and efficient resolution, again accompanied by a polite and friendly attitude.   
I cannot speak highly enough of the staff I had the pleasure of coming into contact with and in a time when it seems the NHS is the butt of criticisms and abuse from all angles they were a shining example of how the NHS can be run and the satisfaction that may be gained by the patient.
My sincere thanks and congratulations for the manner in which you helped me.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
